1a:T78a,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you build custom decks in Ashburn, VA?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Loudoun Decks is one of Ashburn's most trusted deck builders. We serve all Ashburn communities including Brambleton, Broadlands, One Loudoun, and the Ashburn Farm corridor."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the cost of a composite deck in Ashburn?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A professional composite deck in Ashburn typically ranges from $22,000 to $55,000+, depending on size, materials (Trex vs. TimberTech), multi-level design, and add-ons like pergolas or outdoor kitchens."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do Ashburn HOAs approve composite deck designs?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most Ashburn HOAs (Brambleton, Broadlands, etc.) require specific color palettes and structural drawings. We handle all HOA submissions and provide full CAD plans to speed approvals."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How long does it take to build a deck in Ashburn?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Permitting in Loudoun County takes 2-4 weeks. Once approved, most standard decks are completed in 1-2 weeks. Complex multi-level or screened porch projects may take 3-4 weeks of construction."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are you a Trex certified contractor in Ashburn VA?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Loudoun Decks is a Trex Platinum Partner, the highest certification level, giving our Ashburn clients access to the best Trex warranties and the full product catalog."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What outdoor living additions can you build in Ashburn?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Beyond decks, we build screened porches, pergolas, outdoor kitchens, fire pit areas, and multi-level entertainment spaces for Ashburn homeowners seeking full outdoor living transformations."}}]}c:["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","main",null,{"children":[["$